					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-gears" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(172464); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=172464&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610251582" alt="Dr Gears" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=172464)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-gears" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(172464); return false;" >Dr Gears</a></span> <span class="odate time_1491418358 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">05 Apr 2017 18:52</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2784429">
									

<p>Well, I got the internet back, for one. Also, I'm in better shape, physically and mentally, then I've been in years. Been trying to get back into writing in general more, and seeing all the amazing stuff radiating out from the site&#8230;I missed you guys.</p>
<p>I have been picking over the latest batch somewhat, but my immediate recall is garbage. It's weird though, the fact that entries can be just a couple weeks old, and suddenly there's fanart, tribute songs, monotone youtube reviews&#8230;madness. I may have a better reply for you later, once I've been able to dive in more, but I will admit it's hard sometimes. You go though, and get ideas, just to find someone's already done it, and a lot better then you could&#8230;yes, even happens to me.</p>
<p>I'm generally pretty happy with it, it's especially nice to see 682 finally getting a little bit of love, people HATED that thing in the early days. It's always hard to let go the reigns of things you make, but watching how things can evolve and grow naturally is so amazing. The Church started life as a cult that just worshiped SCP items, the clockwork bit just grew organically. I inject my own tone, now and then, like the stories I've done for 106 and such, but generally I love seeing how things grow in another person's hands. I may have the odd quibble with minor bits here and there, but that's the overarching bit.</p>

